    • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

      @Ffaris- There aren't many in England who would say Neuer is anything but a great shot stopper. Anybody who saw his performance for Bayern at the Emirates and his performance in the Germany friendly against England would have to concede he is as good as it gets. De Gea is as good a shot stopper and is the only keeper in the world close to Neuer though. Where Neuer can sometimes fail, and an area where de Gea himself has improved immensely, is commanding the box at set plays. That's not to say he can't/doesn't, but he needs to learn when to come and when to let his defenders clear it themselves. It doesn't help having an unsettled back 4 at Bayern. All of the keepers who command the box at corners, free-kicks etc are those behind a good, settled back 4. The signing of Hummels will help Neuer develop his discernment I'm sure. I think comparing how good both were at the same age (25), de Gea is better but if I were to pick 1 keeper today, it'd be Neuer 100%.

      5 years ago
